<p style="text-align:justify;">July</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">ended.  The adopted son went to his own tent<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Borgne</span> place himself in the Centre of the camp harangued and ordere<span class="AddHand-editors">[d]</span> our party to prepare for their departure.  The weather was extremely hot, water was at a distance and that water was of the filthiest kind &#8212; however necessity obliged us to make use of it since our arrival but at this moment we could procure none.  We applied at Several tents saw plenty of water in bladders but it was refused to us<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  I met a woman with a Bladder full.  I forced it out of her hands and satisfied my thirst from the contents which consisted more of horses dung and urine than of water<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The woman by many attempts struggled to wrest from me this substantial beverage, but I resisted her endeavors until my companions had taken their share also.</p>
